</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dansak>dansak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 12:01:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=273.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When Angels Cried..........7/30 Event</span><hr size=1> I am but a simple pilgrim striving to bring meaning to my life, and in some way to become better for it. What better an example to follow than the great Baron Apep? You may not know it, but I have learned much from you, and for that I offer thanks.<br>
First it was at your marriage to the fair Charizma, where I learnt that the greatest forces in Norrath are hate and love. While I don't believe I am worthy yet to have those words tattoed on the knuckles of my hands; I applaud you for being so enlightened as to be unable to distinguish between the two.<br>
<br>
And now there is the attack on Ak'anon. As you are a noble amongst a noble race, I am forced to reconsider my hatred of my step-brother Prince Bragnar. What I mistook for the childish temper tantrums of a young dog were actually the signs of his nobility. <br>
<br>
I have much to learn, for that reason I will observe the goings on in King Ak'anon's throne room, and hopefully become more enlightened.<br>
<br>
I offer you thanks for the lessons you have taught me, and only wish I had more than words to offer in return. But as I have only words, I offer this:<br>
<br>
Should you succeed in penetrating Ak'anon's defenses, congratulations. You will have succeeded where all of clan Grikbar has failed. You will have elevated the status of Ebon Storm, and indeed all of the Tier'dal, above that of the kobolds of Steamfont.<br>
I wish you the best of luck, and hope that one day you will be looked upon with the same respect as the sabertooths of Blackburrow. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=245548" style="color:#FF6633">Dansak,<br></a>Pilgrim of Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utinxthesummoner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tinx the Summoner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 12:12:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=273.topic&index=26>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When Angels Cried..........7/30 Event</span><hr size=1> Ah, y' twisted elves. Can ye not see that ye'll be accomplishing nothing but th' destruction of knowledge? <br>
